    <item>
      <title>Re: Augments - BiC, Circle of Drakes??</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=TNZ&amp;message.id=245882#M245882</link>
      <description>&lt;a href="http://samanna.net/sham.info/bic.shtml" target=_blank&gt;http://samanna.net/sham.info/bic.shtml&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This is pretty much the only walkthrough to BiC out there.  Its easily the longest quest in the game, but the hard part isn't really the actual events but getting people to help you with them and finding the time to do the innumerable timesinks.  You can do everything up through the mountain trials part of the quest if you aren't in a raid guild, but the reward up to that point is about on par with the Dain Aug, which you could get by doing dain missions all day long until you get all of the pieces of the seal.  To get the BiC aug up to that level would represent hundreds of hours of work.  Once you finish up with Kod`Taz and Yxtta though, its pretty much smooth sailing, assuming you are in a raiding guild, since they only require 1 drop from a raid mob for each zone.  The most probable thing to block you after that is the Txevu drop.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I don't feel that the final reward is really worth it, but IMO the quest is more for those who just enjoy questing in general.</description>
